{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-single-blog-js","path":"/blogs/designing-human-powered-car","result":{"data":{"sanityBlog":{"title":"Designing Human-Powered Cars","_rawBody":[{"_key":"13915b2f6099","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"b369b4942ad70","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"This is a hypothetical scenario in which cars are powered by human energy rather than gasoline or other fuel sources."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"3be8a525fde2","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"19eee68884c30","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"In this design challenge, you would need to consider how to create a car that could be pedaled or cranked by humans to get around. You might start by researching existing human-powered vehicles, such as bicycles or pedal-powered rickshaws, and think about how you could adapt those designs for a larger, more robust vehicle."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"b60ff9b5ca20","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"24a5114e10920","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"You would also need to consider factors like ergonomics (i.e. how to make the vehicle comfortable and efficient for human use), safety (i.e. how to protect drivers and passengers in the event of a crash), and performance (i.e. how fast and far the vehicle can travel on human power)."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"46a0afc47c71","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"841cbf6cbc680","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"This design challenge could be a fun and creative way to explore alternative forms of transportation and think about the ways in which we use energy in our daily lives. It could also be an opportunity to consider the environmental and social implications of our current transportation systems, and to brainstorm ways to make transportation more sustainable and accessible to all."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"}],"coverImage":{"asset":{"gatsbyImageData":{"images":{"sources":[],"fallback":{"src":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/bmgmvqmz/pr